This paper is about improving the performance of Neural Machine Translation (NMT) models through multi-agent learning. The paper discusses the use of diverse agents in an interactive updating process to improve translation quality. This work involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of advanced knowledge and learning from others, which are common themes in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The use of multiple agents and interactive updating also suggests the relevance of the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of image captioning as a potential application of the proposed approach, which suggests the relevance of the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
